<TITLE> 69 more 'harassment' cases to be dropped </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 15 (bdnews24.com)Sixty-nine more cases filed for political persecution will be dropped, the head of the scrutiny committee that recommended withdrawal of the charges said on Wednesday. "We have decided to withdraw another 69 cases," Kamrul Islam, the committee chairman and the state minister for law, told reporters. Of them, 56 were filed under penal code while the remaining 13 by the Anticorruption Commission, Islam said after the committee's fourth meeting. Wednesday's meeting recommended quashing cases against Awami League leaders Mohiuddin Khan Alamgir and Tofail Ahmed and Daily Janakantha editor Atiqullah Khan Masud. The committee has so far recommended 174 cases to be quashed since its first sitting last month. Its first meeting on June 10 recommended cancellation of 62 cases, including 12 against prime minister Sheikh Hasina. On June 21 it approved another 46 cases to be cancelled and on July 1, in its third meeting, the committee recommended 66 cases. bd
